This paper discusses the comparison of bibliometric journal evaluation products, which involves analyzing and processing large amounts of data related to scientific publications. This aligns with several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and cryptography (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses on the evaluation of scientific journals, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.CY, and cs.CR.
